{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","roleHeading":"API Collection","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Guides","generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Related","anchor":"Related","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SharedFolder","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawTemplate"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is an open-source self-hosted AI assistant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that connects to Claude, GPT-4, Gemini, and other models. Running OpenClaw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in macOS VMs with Spooktacular gives you:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolation"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — each instance has its own macOS environment, API keys,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and workspace. A misconfigured agent can’t affect the other."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2 instances per Mac"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — Apple Silicon’s 2-VM kernel limit maps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"perfectly to running a pair of agents (e.g., work + personal,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or production + staging)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — save a working OpenClaw configuration, experiment,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and roll back if something breaks."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Kubernetes-managed"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — scale OpenClaw instances across a fleet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of Macs using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MacOSVMPool"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"text":"Prerequisites","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Prerequisites"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14+ on the host"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular installed ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"brew install --cask spooktacular"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"API key from Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google"}]}]}]},{"text":"Quick Start: Two OpenClaw Instances","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Quick-Start-Two-OpenClaw-Instances"},{"level":3,"anchor":"1-Create-the-first-VM","type":"heading","text":"1. Create the first VM"},{"code":["spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 32 \\","    --network nat \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh \\","    --provision disk-inject"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"level":3,"anchor":"2-Clone-for-the-second-instance","type":"heading","text":"2. Clone for the second instance"},{"code":["spook clone openclaw-work openclaw-personal"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The clone takes ~50ms (APFS copy-on-write). Each VM gets a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unique machine identifier automatically."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"3-Start-both","type":"heading","text":"3. Start both"},{"code":["spook start openclaw-work --headless","spook start openclaw-personal --headless"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both VMs boot and run OpenClaw independently. Each listens"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on its own IP address, port 18789."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"4-Check-status","type":"heading","text":"4. Check status"},{"code":["spook list","spook ip openclaw-work","spook ip openclaw-personal"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"level":2,"anchor":"User-Data-Script-for-OpenClaw","type":"heading","text":"User-Data Script for OpenClaw"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a script that installs and configures OpenClaw automatically:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# setup-openclaw.sh — installs OpenClaw in a macOS VM","","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Homebrew (if not present)","if ! command -v brew &>\/dev\/null; then","    \/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","    eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","fi","","# Install Node.js 24","brew install node@24","echo 'export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"' >> ~\/.zshrc","export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","","# Install OpenClaw","npm install -g openclaw@latest","","# Run onboard with daemon installation","# (The API key should be set via environment variable or","#  injected via the shared folder)","openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","echo \"OpenClaw installed and running on port 18789\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For production deployments, pass the API key via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a shared folder or environment variable rather than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hardcoding it in the script."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Passing-API-Keys-Securely","type":"heading","text":"Passing API Keys Securely"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a shared folder to deliver configuration without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"embedding secrets in the script:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# On the host: create a config directory","mkdir -p ~\/openclaw-configs\/work","cat > ~\/openclaw-configs\/work\/openclaw.json << 'EOF'","{","    \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514\",","    \"anthropicApiKey\": \"sk-ant-your-key-here\"","}","EOF","","# Create VM with shared folder","spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --share ~\/openclaw-configs\/work:config:ro \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh"],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the setup script, copy the config from the shared folder:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Inside setup-openclaw.sh","mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/openclaw.json","openclaw config validate"],"syntax":"bash"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Kubernetes-OpenClaw-Fleet","text":"Kubernetes: OpenClaw Fleet"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy OpenClaw instances across multiple Macs using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Kubernetes operator:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["apiVersion: spooktacular.io\/v1alpha1","kind: MacOSVMPool","metadata:","  name: openclaw-agents","  namespace: ai","spec:","  replicas: 2","  image: ghcr.io\/spooktacular\/macos:15.4","","  provisioning:","    mode: disk-inject","    userData: |","      #!\/bin\/bash","      brew install node@24","      export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","      npm install -g openclaw@latest","      mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","      # Config injected via K8s secret → shared folder","      cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/","      openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","  resources:","    cpu: 4","    memory: 8Gi","    disk: 32Gi","","  network:","    mode: nat"],"syntax":"yaml"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each Mac in the fleet runs 2 OpenClaw VMs. Ten Macs ="},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"20 OpenClaw instances."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Networking-Between-Instances","text":"Networking Between Instances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your OpenClaw instances need to communicate (e.g.,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a coordinator agent delegating to worker agents):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook create openclaw-coordinator --from-ipsw latest --network nat","spook create openclaw-worker --from-ipsw latest --network nat"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"NAT networking lets the VMs reach each other via their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"DHCP-assigned IPs and the host Mac. The coordinator can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reach the worker’s gateway on port 18789. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated"},{"type":"text","text":" if you need to prevent internet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"access entirely, communicating through shared folders"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the VirtIO socket instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For internet access + inter-VM communication, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NAT networking — both VMs can reach each other via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their NAT-assigned IPs."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Resource-Planning","text":"Resource Planning"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CPU"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Memory"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Disk"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notes"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cloud models only"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 cores"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimal — OpenClaw is lightweight"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cloud + light local models"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 cores"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"8 GB","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"32 GB","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ollama with small models","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Heavy local models (Llama 3)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"6 cores"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"64 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Needs unified memory"}]}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since macOS VMs share the host’s unified memory via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Virtualization framework, the GPU (Metal) is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"available inside the VM for local model inference."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Monitoring","text":"Monitoring"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check OpenClaw health in each VM:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# From the host","spook ssh openclaw-work -- \"openclaw status\"","spook ssh openclaw-personal -- \"openclaw status\"","","# Or via the gateway API","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-work):18789\/health","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-personal):18789\/health"],"syntax":"bash"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Snapshots","text":"Snapshots"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Save a working OpenClaw configuration before making changes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The VM must be stopped to take or restore a disk-level snapshot:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook stop openclaw-work","spook snapshot openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless","# ... make changes, install new version ...","# If something breaks:","spook stop openclaw-work","spook restore openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless"],"syntax":"bash"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide"},"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","title":"Machine Learning Workloads","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/mlworkloads","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/NetworkMode":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}],"title":"NetworkMode","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The network configuration mode for a virtual machine."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted